<TITLE> Internal BCL rivalry escalates at RUET </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  Rivalry between two groups within the Bangladesh Chhatra League at Rajshahi University of Engineering Technology escalated on Wednesday night as supporters of the two groups clashed. Witnesses said supporters of Al Amin and Harun-or-Rashid attacked the two followers of Rezaul Islam Reza in front of Shahidullah hall at around 11pm. This followed a previous incident on Apr 22 when the same group are alleged to have attacked four followers of Reza group Two activists, Rubel and Shaheen, were injured and admitted to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital. Police arrested Al Amin, Harun, Reza and Akram following the incident. They were released on bail. Reza told reporters that some eight to ten activists led by Harun assaulted Rubel and Shaeen and escaped the scene. Other students helped to admit them to hospital, he said. Al Amin and Harun were not available for comments. Motihar police chief Tofazzal Hosain Khan said they went to the campus hearing the news. Additional policemen have been deployed on the campus to avoid further untoward incident, he said. bd
